ABOUT THE SCRIPT

The script 'run_analysis.R' does the following functions:
•First, it merges the training and the test sets by using rbind()
•I used grep() to find a subset of features, which have "[Mm]ean" or "[Ss]td" in their names.
•By using gsub(), I renamed some of the column names to make them more descriptive.
•cbind() was used to combine subject.data("subject") and y.data("activity")
•colnames() was used to change labels of subject.data and y.data to "subject" and "activity" respectively.
•aggregate() with mean() was used to find the average of each variable for each activity and each subject.

